[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Identifying API features**\n\nI need to add a new feature that isn't currently covered. Right now, I have various RFC patch operations involving JSON, like adding, replacing, and moving elements, as well as handling errors and merges. Now, I need to identify what part of the public API isn't addressed. I'm considering the json-patch 1.13 library, which has a JsonDiff.asJsonMergePatch feature. I wonder if I need to factor in equivalence or reverse patching? I think I'll need to inspect the API further, possibly using javap or a jar file.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ed4afd52a55eae30169f61a0e4b688194a04d4fe39e839a60\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9hoT_pe52VQl-VCJCK82A24InEFG2EfRKKnZce9i11JiJveGjK99y5JWAxJKGXVIC49dh0qSPd0t0xO_0bbK5bvPIhEF_Ueo33JvsFbvFqcXSfGA2ycrWtQavpeRImmwwG6XQveByoF1O0m_CYNdbkY8nn3UY4kYkZojSdFUROw9hiN3xQzoPA_b6_ZH1Tf-kQoqsHpOs7-pRKOqAUanRJq22oVj8_IlxVFjT0OrwW929tI7goUupsgg8Eze_t1nu8fkEwYMzb6FHdPDOaymKxNlW7LQRPTK4BYwQ4QqqZjo0CnYBXp_nl1EHJJdE2xztURRgKqUYARxn4W3mZx2EqClh67tiTX1XSE-SkpY9p2y5OY8nr-jTpI9BbNUYDqd1abmaeX1ivTyus4jfmkEX-rERpuhylGfDEqH2qyzKczqPnBpy_dnqzVTO8c1WZ_lnmfF_LuvuTriJNFZqROkqAmFPz9COekcscfm2shE5qoFjXaC1s-s-5osIBeo1zaAWMCHV8pPl7IaaySl63jw9lqYbIvmoC6b9ZX2f_BSS850ZygxBiNrQ2QggP62dKLW79NzZEkSHU9q2y4y34iinZYzaZOvB-8V8q8UPGI8_k3UDl7cog7gwYJ3GbUnUmXkmd51xTYOSf8LIIFWYgKJel8eZy_CaoxXhUjQnEW5iZ847Ltzh27zKAcZSZgOfs_kCoEMKlqdyLGyw5_Vp9CcxYgHD3LUmuI-mGrXNPcBjp99MLSzMbQjF3vKKM98MeDQr6QuLQLOVR4i3AzlesNl-NV6e3JRsHAjt913j8wpMqsEqj0gPoi2MPpUFzY0NkFb418ACUEBZsVqxOuNnXck49bik7rmk7g6oMV6ywCp0Tf_3qbiOZ-ST7tyn5LjWSyOdFUvSkw8JCDZsi-wnpt3bgZSDRLRcRXN6xCjkWY-BWAHGUyaE4Nfm636A3Ma1lAaZvumeTQcxA9-swY3_5vPK7yL8T1gT8ojoD7mRUxl61HLzvNuuHEPN0Pr1-nta7-c-VURgxF-9cqbICbB97DeUJNX8Er43-BgN1jME9AVP6xf0utRxryEP7IhaOozs1srwdLN5Taso7_uqUdLKN9tUCvIH26nA5qBrFfrfNQdddYKzwhtpS0MCmz6bVuiSVaD1Q5QVQHQCwLwyp_e7UVYmSqNsUs_L8ZWfCl5to-bPWMLFZO6LpQ