[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring diff copy/move features**\n\nI’m considering using diff to implement copy/move as a feature. The existing JSON patch operations include copy and move, but diff’s detection isn’t quite there. I feel like it makes sense for JsonDiff to reuse unchanged values as \"copy\" and to treat remove plus add as \"move.\" This could factor in robust deterministic testing. I need to make sure that the `getUnchangedValues` order is clear, especially since the unchanged values can lead to unpredictability. I might check the decompiled code to understand how the map for unchanged values is structured.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ed4afd52a55eae30169f61a214ccc8194a457b84f12716efd\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9homA4V0UOssJpe8TygNfg93xarP1Xi8OIrsDmEgE5LU_lwZJEaNnc88VXaeOWNOkR83nsFWcJSbXKasvx9me42gQxJJms4LAmVQKYYRPajUGfz97OjxI5G1QIfRsLzYyfWU5-vwEKpBVaMtRS9wbrIW7QPcknoSc28W50Tft53LWNXOlIFXUkiuu3nfolbTCtlecGCrLptmFiZHGWhxWDEzLYVTPGL8jXFUvG3ZtjRZj7K8IdtGMqyYFABzBS2AyF0uISoz8rG5q4bwsaGohHKI7eC08VpiT3nf6GyXu4vQw8o-cqOneTcWOEqzgZYsSurZouwPEeWX1Irim8gIidUMT-ErWJ8RqTwswoyvuUR6te_z-0eXh4LBDoTSDfDXoL_W0WhDrErJy-11nz7u6O9qfjYDPllIY22ru8XJKZ16ioXu81T1Etyn2bNXDQnv2eU_3Xis8vklro8UfstGRkL7h9PxlcZ3CJWv-3qXPy17Y0msvEy7QzsTVZyTBynpWuTDJrFxgSImc5cLDBPhwixdqI4oWeVBR48DJ0wUYGEF6urxGUO7JsS5K1u68WAphdL1vxsBV9JN5nXJrJhp8e6d4LpKTp0hgckwlStSq0D82HUoJk6h7LbZITBniv3pI6ioHNM86pOuQn2aGUAqhwWZDBOSU0lnJX_3W2Hodm5KBNkC8i5LzXIixYP0GzfFOKN7wU169OpjC6jRa0RuzA-DHuCCr2xOAGsZSfHk43kj3NFvS1yF09dCRlbQAncAiLpdfRkoSbOWCi_PSGFoUfRjROhM67BQyVisvVBGthffKFYT8qvdxSDIg6Kozz7nrdidTbD1V8nLwBuZgtxMLVKlakwEYig4otjGImsJlgrKz1m0EHHLgurbQUOy18ho3c57AJa-GY4KaMTLUN1myMivtb0Kn56XqXyDka1gXIo9Hq3DkrPQKLvAHEGTk_qZNSmrx9GIeh8LwQuusXrRcx6nxy75A5Ovh4kRUYzLd1IC-_nt_f6_Jvd1tIKjs0g7KEt1w9iLhjjDfdr4TltCx3Yu-zA6s5tQlZ3aAOxxARRiX2wGdzeVYAzX7jmBHC8pcGgS7Gp91RQaXMramOC9mmgWhzPaMtkWcRGi9T1yzavw8J1RtnQdF30A